yesterday afternoon , beijing holding football club ( hereinafter referred to as north control ) made an official response to the news that Anichebe , former foreign aid to the team , had accused the team of playing fake football . the north control issued a statement , saying that the club absolutely did not have any cases of kicking fake balls . this was completely a lie fabricated by Anichebe himself during the arbitration process in order to cover up his flagrant violation of the contract and for his personal and improper economic purpose .
at the same time , north control said it would reserve the right to pursue the responsibility of the parties concerned by all means .
Nigerian player Anichebe has accused FIFA of playing bogus football last year , including Beijing &apos;s Derby for the 21st round in mid @-@ 2017 , the Daily Mail reported .
it was a crucial stage for the Beijing people and the Premier League , and the game ended with a 0 @-@ 2 defeat for the Beijing people and Arnichebi .
the Nigerian player &apos;s statement was met with an official response from the club yesterday .
the statement said that after the club &apos;s previous internal investigations , the team has participated in the game did not play fake ball .
Anichebe joined Beijing in June 2017 . in December of the same year , Anichebe refused to return to winter training without justification and refused to do so despite repeated reminders from the club .
at present , the dispute between the two sides has been submitted to FIFA and arbitration is under way .
