Chinese state councilor and foreign minister Wang Yi said in a speech to the us committee on foreign relations on friday : at present , sino - us relations have once again come to a crossroads . if the two sides can positively embrace each other , expand positive cooperation , and properly manage their differences and contradictions , they will open up better prospects .
" China - us relations are our common assets and we need to take care of them together . "
he expressed the hope that people of insight from all walks of life in the two countries will take concrete action to maintain the healthy and stable development of sino - us relations and jointly push sino - us relations forward in the correct direction .
Wang Yi also stressed again that china will certainly follow a different development path from the traditional big powers .
this road with chinese characteristics has determined that china will not , and will not , repeat the mistake of becoming a strong country and a hegemonic power . it has also determined that china will not become the united states , challenge the united states , and still less replace the united states .
in his speech entitled " opportunities or challenges , partners or adversaries , " Wang Yi said : the deep - seated crux of the problem at present lies in the fact that some american friends believe that china will also become a strong country and will even challenge and replace the united states in its leading position in the world .
&quot; this is clearly a major strategic miscalculation . &quot;
but this self @-@ imagined suspicion is spreading , amplifying existing contradictions , creating new doubts and making it more difficult and difficult for China and the United States to resolve specific problems , he said .
Wang Yi pointed out : China has taken a road of peaceful development .
the Chinese have never had any genes for external expansion .
we believe that all countries can coexist in harmony and learn from each other .
whether in the past , now , or in the future , china will neither copy the foreign model nor ask other countries to copy china 's practice .
earlier , when Wang Yi met with former us secretary of state Henry Kissinger in new york , he said that sino - us cooperation will win - win and confrontation will lose and lose .
China has always been committed to developing long @-@ term , healthy and stable China @-@ US relations , so as to achieve non @-@ conflict , non @-@ confrontation , mutual respect and win @-@ win cooperation .
the state council of china held a news conference Tuesday to introduce and interpret the white paper " facts about sino - us economic and trade frictions and china 's stance . "
Chinese vice minister of commerce fu ziyong said at the news conference that china is willing to make efforts to push bilateral trade toward a more balanced direction and hopes that the us side will also show a positive posture .
chinanews , oct 1 - according to foreign media reports , indonesia 's Sulawesi island was hit by a strong earthquake and tsunami on september 28 , causing serious damage to several cities along the coast . the latest news shows that the number of people killed has risen to 1,200 .
authorities believe the death toll will continue to rise as the &quot; golden 72 hours &quot; of rescue efforts pass , following reports of two rounds of tsunami strikes in the town of Donggara , near the epicenter of the quake .
on September 30 , 2018 , local time , in Palu , Central Sulawesi Province , Indonesia , rescuers carried an earthquake survivor rescued from the ruins of a restaurant .
officials at the disaster relief department said the tsunami caused a huge wave of up to six meters , and the earthquake and tsunami affected more people than originally estimated .
hundreds of people were celebrating the holiday on the beach in Palu when the quake and tsunami struck , and many died when the waves swept away .
officials say the tsunami hit the shore at 800 kilometers an hour , destroying many buildings and infrastructure .
he said thousands of homes , hospitals , shopping malls and hotels collapsed , and a tsunami @-@ triggered mudslide cut off one of the main roads in Palu .
a bridge across a coastal river collapsed in Sulawesi .
on september 30 , local time , Indonesian president Joko inspected the city of central Sulawesi Palu , where the earthquake occurred .
Indonesian president Joko visited the disaster area on september 30 , saying troops had been dispatched to help rescue the victims and called on them to be patient .
Zoko pointed out that the rescue operation was very difficult because of the shortage of heavy machinery and manpower .
he noted that many of the affected areas lacked supplies such as water , food and fuel , and that a large number of businesses had closed down after the earthquake and had sent aircraft to drop supplies .
he appealed to the victims to be patient and to stay where they were and wait for help .
rescue workers in Palu city said they heard calls for help coming from a collapsed hotel in the city , but were unable to move the rubble because there was no heavy machine and some people needed help in vain .
Indonesia &apos;s vice president , Kara , says the death toll from the earthquake and tsunami could eventually rise to thousands as electricity and communications are cut off in some areas and information is blocked .
Shenyang , november 5 ( reporter Xu Zhiqiang , Yan Yi - na ) the reporter learned today from the Liaoning provincial court that during the six - month campaign to carry out the " storm , " the Liaoning provincial court sternly cracked down on those who refused to carry out the act and handed over 241 people who refused to carry out the crime , thus maintaining the high - pressure situation of cracking down on those who refused to carry out the crime .
it has been learned that according to the unified arrangements of the Liaoning supreme people 's court , from early april to the end of september , the Liaoning court launched a six - month campaign to basically resolve the difficulties in implementing the " storm , " amassing superior forces , and launching an all - round general attack on the difficulties in implementing the basic resolution .
at the same time , courts throughout the province organized and carried out " five groups " of activities to impose fines , detain one batch , restrict one batch of consumption , punish one batch of people for breach of trust , and transfer one batch of people to refuse to commit crimes .
at the beginning of the activity , there were more than 132,000 outstanding cases in the provincial courts , and at the end of july , the cases were closed to the public .
during the activities , courts across the province imposed fines of 12.006 million yuan , detained 4,146 people , restricted consumption of 162,844 people , punished 55,128 people for dishonesty , and transferred 241 people for refusing to detain .
from january to october this year , the Liaoning court handled a total of 297,438 enforcement cases , an increase of 13.28 percent over the same period of last year ; it closed 226,558 cases , an increase of 83.18 percent over the same period last year ; and implemented 31.236 billion yuan , an increase of 74.94 percent over the same period last year .
