she had been in hong kong by bus for a long time , but it took time and effort . she worried that her son 's condition would be affected . this time , she was even more impressed by the convenience of taking a high - speed railway through Shenzhen and the halving of the time spent . she told the reporter : " it seems that i could not take a picture before taking a subway ride . "
on 23 September , at 6.44 a.m. , the G5711 &quot; Harmony &quot; high @-@ speed rail train started from Shenzhen North Station and raced all the way . a few minutes later , the train entered the Hong Kong section of the Guangzhou @-@ Shenzhen High @-@ speed Railway , the first fully operational high @-@ speed rail train in Hong Kong .
it will be integrated into the country 's 25,000 - km high - speed rail network , reaching the hong kong section of the 38 long - distance railway stations across the country , and will also welcome mainland tourists from different provinces , south and north of the country .
Mr. Gao , who came to visit his relatives in hong kong from Changsha on a long holiday , told this reporter : before , the high - speed railway could only sit in Shenzhen north , take a subway to cross the border from hong kong , and then travel around the city . he was in trouble and time - consuming transportation . now he can sit directly in the center of Kowloon and get home to eat his children 's lunch . he feels very happy .
he said that the " one place , two checks " customs procedures were more convenient than imagined , " less than 10 minutes later , both were over . "
