xinjing bao ( reporter ni wei ) -- the general administration of radio , television , and telecommunications issued the " circular on launching special rectification work for radio and television advertisements " on 29 september , starting from now until the end of this year , to launch special rectification work for radio and television advertisements .
the content of the rectification includes low @-@ standard , low @-@ quality and low @-@ grade advertising , undocumented management of the broadcast of the issue of health care programs .
according to the circular , the current special rectification work focuses on nine aspects .
in particular , there are advertisements with problems of orientation ; advertisements with low contents and low quality ; advertisements with problems of excessive time and failure to broadcast according to regulations ; and advertisements with problems of exaggeration , misinformation , or publication in disguised form with problems of medical treatment , medicine , cosmetic products , cosmetic products , and other problems ;
the current rectification work will be completely covered throughout the country , and the requirements for rectification and standardization will be fully implemented in radio and television media at all levels , in the frequency of channels , and in the program columns and time slots , and " there will be no blind spots , no dead ends , no exceptions . "
the circular demands that the administrative departments of radio and television broadcasting at all levels strictly follow the " procedures for handling illegal and irregular advertisements discovered by radio and television broadcasting organizations . "
those who violate the regulations in serious cases should be severely dealt with , such as commanding speeches , circulating criticisms , suspending the broadcasting of advertisements , and even suspending the broadcasting of frequency channels , and exposed to the public according to the circumstances .
in recent years , the General Administration of Radio , Television and Television has repeatedly called for the suspension of illegal advertising .
this year , the state administration of radio and television issued a circular publicly calling for the suspension of advertisements for serious violations such as " 0 kimchi milk , " " shava cocktail , " " banritt plant anti - sterile hair dew , " and so on , which contained misguided and exaggerated propaganda and misled the audience .
the general administration of radio , television and television has formulated a number of regulations and circulars to regulate the conduct of radio and television advertisements .
the " circular on further strengthening the management of advertisements for television shopping clips broadcast by tv channels " stipulates that tv channels are not allowed to broadcast advertisements for television shopping clips from 18:00 to 24:00 every day .
when broadcasting advertisements for short television shopping clips during other periods , we must not use the moderator to publicize them ; we must not use such propaganda as " hawking " to exaggerate the sound , tone , and movement ; we must not use such propaganda as " orthopaedic , " " plastic , " " lipid permeability , " and " flipping " to publicize breast enlargement , weight - loss products , and we must not broadcast advertisements for short television shopping clips every hour of the day for more than one ( one ) , each not exceeding three minutes .
the Circular on Further Strengthening the Administration of Radio and Television Advertising stipulates that when a television station interrupts an advertisement in the middle of a movie or television series , it must strictly abide by the provisions of General Directorate Decree No. 61 , which stipulates that two commercial advertisements may be inserted in each episode of non @-@ prime time ( 45 minutes ) , each time not exceeding 1 minute and 30 seconds ; the prime time ( 19 : 00 to 21 : 00 ) may not exceed 1 minute for each episode of commercial advertising ; and the advertisement shall be preceded by one minute .
the circular also stipulates that radio and television broadcasting organizations should strictly examine the qualifications and certificates of health information advertisements , such as medical treatment , pharmaceuticals , medical devices , and health food products , and resolutely prohibit the broadcasting of sex - related advertisements .
to standardize the form of health information advertising , no advertisements should be published in disguised form in the form of health information feature programmes .
health information special programs should focus on introducing scientific knowledge such as disease prevention , control , and treatment , and should not contain advertisements on medical treatment , pharmaceuticals , medical devices , health food , etc . , and should not be certified in the name of patients , doctors , pharmacists , and experts .
