ignore the American threat !
EU to reach agreement with iran on crude oil procurement
the US government has announced that it will reintroduce a new round of sanctions against Iran in November , even urging other countries to reduce imports of Iranian oil .
but America &apos;s allies do not seem to listen .
according to a report in the new york times , Iranian foreign minister Zarif disclosed during an interview on 29 april that Tehran was close to reaching an agreement with the european union on the sale of crude oil , despite the threat of sanctions by the united states against any country doing business with iran .
the core purpose of the agreement is to try to create a new payment mechanism , that is , to replace dollar transactions with barter or local currency .
the aim of this approach is to circumvent the United States and prevent it from impeding financial transfers .
at the same time , while the European Union is working to broker the agreement , some French and British officials are concerned that , if it materializes , it would be the most open confrontation between the European Union and the United States , which opposes the withdrawal of the United States from the nuclear agreement .
in a one @-@ hour interview , Zarif &apos;s words sounded more optimistic than in recent months , US media said .
the deal is capable of &quot; stripping &quot; America of its traditional allies and effectively disrupting US attempts to cut Iran &apos;s revenues .
&quot; this will ensure that we sell and benefit from oil , &quot; Zarif said , arguing that countries have a legitimate right to trade with Iran under the agreement reached in 2015 .
Fedrica Moguerini , head of eu foreign policy , also said a few days ago : " no sovereign state or organization can accept others to decide who it can trade with . "
but she also predicts that , before the next sanctions are imposed by the US government in November , US leaders could adopt a range of financial measures aimed at targeting banks , businessmen , and countries doing business with Tehran .
in May , the US government unilaterally announced its withdrawal from the Iran nuclear agreement , citing defects in the agreement , saying it would not permanently ban Iran from producing nuclear fuel .
the United States then threatened to ban companies that bought Iranian oil and other goods from doing business in the United States .
the threat caused some companies to leave Tehran and the Iranian currency plummeted .
companies such as Airbus and French oil giant Doudale have canceled billions of dollars of investment in Iraq .
British and french officials have said that the us government may " prevail . "
indeed , according to a recent report in the Turkish media , the US sanctions do not appear to have had a significant impact on Iran &apos;s oil exports .
Iranian oil minister Zangane revealed recently that no other country except south korea has stopped buying Iranian oil .
both Zarif and Iranian president Hosni Rouhani believe that the purpose of a series of us actions is to " lure " iran into violating the agreement .
Zarif also disdained the series of verbal attacks by the united states . when asked whether the united states would overthrow the current Iranian government with increasing financial pressure , Zarif even laughed . " it is a strategy of regime change , and this is the real goal of the united states . "
