the state council recently issued the " decision on further reducing the catalogue of production licenses for industrial products and simplifying the examination and approval procedures , " which was signed and approved by premier li keqiang .
the " decision " proposes further reducing the catalogue of management of production licenses for industrial products , abolishing the management of production licenses for 14 types of industrial products , and decentralizing the management of production licenses for four types of industrial products to the quality and technical supervision departments of provincial people 's governments .
as a result of this reform , the number of products under the control of production licenses for industrial products will be reduced from 38 last year to 24 at present .
the Decision makes it clear that the approval procedure for products in the catalogue should be simplified .
the first is to replace the pre @-@ license product inspection organized by the issuing authority with the product inspection qualification report issued by the qualified inspection and inspection organization at the time of application .
second , with the exception of dangerous chemicals , the products licensed by the quality and technical supervision departments of provincial people 's governments ( market supervision and administration departments ) are subject to on - the - spot examination . after enterprises submit applications and product inspection qualification reports and make commitments to ensure product quality and safety , they can obtain production licenses through formal examination and then undergo on - the - spot examination within a specified time .
third , when an enterprise applies for a new license or applies for the renewal of a license , it shall examine and issue a license certificate in accordance with the principle of " one enterprise , one license " for different categories of products in its production and operation catalog .
the " decision " requires all localities and relevant departments to make solid efforts to promote the work of reducing the catalog and simplifying the examination and approval procedures .
we will increase the intensity of enterprises ' efforts to publicize their promises and conduct on - site examination after they are announced , strengthen the means of credit supervision and restraint , implement the principal responsibility of enterprises for quality , and revoke all production licenses if they fail to meet the requirements .
with regard to products that are subject to the abolition of production licenses for industrial products , it is necessary to conscientiously strengthen supervision after the event . products related to public health and safety and environmental protection may be turned into compulsory certification , positive lists may be drawn up and made public to the public , standards for certification should be unified , items for testing should be reasonably reduced and certified , and the cost of compulsory certification should , in principle , be borne by the financial authorities at all levels according to the system .
adopt support measures to encourage enterprises to carry out voluntary certification , promote brand building and expand the market .
it is necessary to meet international advanced standards and promote the improvement of the quality of industrial products .
give full play to the role of third party social organizations to ensure the safety of industrial product quality .
with regard to products under the management of production licenses for industrial products , it is necessary to improve the standard system , give play to the advantages of industry supervision , strengthen the responsibility of " who approves and supervises , who supervises , " dynamically assess product quality safety risks , promptly reduce catalogues , decentralize examination and approval authority , or turn into certification management .
China &apos;s Integrated PMI Ring boosted manufacturing PMI Ring down in September .
China 's composite PMI output index stood at 54.1 percent in september , up from 0.3 percentage points and 0.1 percentage points in the previous month and the annual average , according to the national bureau of statistics ( nbs ) .
the manufacturing production index and the non - manufacturing business activity index , which made up the composite PMI output index , were 53.0 percent and 54.9 percent , respectively , down one litre from the previous month .
of this , china 's manufacturing PMI was 50.8 percent , down 0.5 percentage points from the previous year .
Mr Zhao said there were five main features of the manufacturing PMI this month :
first , manufacturing fundamentals are generally stable .
of the 21 industries surveyed , 14 had PMIs in the expansion zone , and manufacturing PMIs such as pharmaceuticals , specialized equipment , and electrical and mechanical equipment all had a relatively high operating level of over 53.5 percent , with faster growth rates .
second , supply and demand fluctuated slightly .
the index of production and the index of new orders were 53.0 percent and 52.0 percent respectively , down 0.3 and 0.2 percentage points from the previous month , and supply and demand remained buoyant , but the expansion slowed slightly .
the new export orders index and import index were 48.0 percent and 48.5 percent , respectively , down from 1.4 percentage points and 0.6 percentage points in the previous month , and both fell to their lowest levels during the year .
fourth , the cost of purchasing raw materials for enterprises has increased .
the main raw materials purchasing price index was 59.8 percent , up 1.1 percentage points from the previous month , and the factory price index was 54.3 percent , the same as last month , all high in the year .
fifth , large enterprises run steadily , and small enterprises continue to improve their business conditions .
the PMI of large companies , at 52.1 per cent , remained at 52.0 per cent and above this year , and both the production index and the new order index rose this month , the main driving force behind manufacturing expansion ; the PMI of medium @-@ sized companies , at 48.7 per cent , was 1.7 percentage points lower than the previous month and was in the contraction zone ; and the PMI of small businesses , at 50.4 per cent , was 0.4 percentage points higher than the previous month , rising for two consecutive months .
that month , China &apos;s non @-@ manufacturing business activity index rose 0.7 percentage points from last month to 54.9 per cent , rebounding for the second month in a row .
Zhao Qinghe believes that the non - manufacturing industry as a whole continues to maintain a steady and positive development momentum .
road transport , securities , real estate and other industries continue to be below the critical point of business activity index , total business volume has been reduced .
Nagoya , Nov. 5 ( Reuters ) - The Bank of Japan is aware that a prolonged period of ultra @-@ easy monetary policy could squeeze financial institutions &quot; profit margins and destabilize the country &apos;s banking system , central bank chief Yoshihiko Kuroda said Monday .
but , given low inflation and uncertainty in overseas economies , he said , the BOJ needed to maintain its massive stimulus package while keeping a close eye on the pros and cons of its policies .
&quot; the BOJ fully acknowledges that the strength of financial institutions will be increasingly affected by continued monetary easing , &quot; Mr Kuroda said in a speech to business leaders in Nagoya .
if financial institutions are more aggressive in taking on the risks to compensate for years of low interest rates that have narrowed margins , he said , the banking system could become volatile in the event of a severe negative shock .
&quot; although these risks are small at the moment , the central bank will closely monitor developments and encourage financial institutions to take the necessary measures , &quot; he said .
the BOJ &apos;s policy committee discussed the rising costs of long @-@ term easing at its September meeting , according to minutes of a meeting of the Bank of Japan &apos;s central bank announced earlier Monday .
the minutes show that if the economy continues to expand , &quot; the Bank of Japan has more room for policy flexibility in the future . &quot;
the minutes showed that another member said the committee should discuss how long the BOJ could keep the stimulus policy going , given its limitations over the duration of the policy .
Mr Kuroda said the BOJ would assess the financial risks of easing , while also considering the uncertainty surrounding Japan &apos;s economic outlook , given the potential impact of trade frictions and rising protectionism between China and the US on global demand .
&quot; the impact of such problems on Japan &apos;s economy is limited for the time being , &quot; Mr Kuroda said .
&quot; but how the problem persists is likely to have a greater impact on Japan &apos;s economy , &quot; he added .
&quot; there is a need for strong monetary easing on a sustained basis , taking into account both positive and negative effects in a balanced manner , &quot; Kuroda said .
while there has been an increase in the malaise of aggressive stimulus packages , such as long @-@ term low interest rates that erode the profitability of financial institutions , low inflation has forced the BOJ to maintain the program .
the Bank of Japan maintained monetary policy last month ; Mr Kuroda ruled out a recent rate hike in the face of the risks posed by the war end of global trade .
corporate logo on the Tesla electric car , Cardiff , USA , June 1 , 2018 .
under a settlement agreement , Tesla Motor and its chief executive , Maske , have agreed to pay a $ 20 million fine each to the financial regulator , and Maske will resign as chairman of the company but remain a CEO .
the settlement agreement will end two months of unrest in Tesla .
the securities fraud settlement , revealed by the Securities and Exchange Commission on Saturday , will give investors a sigh of relief .
investors had feared that a protracted legal battle would only further hit the still @-@ losing electric car company .
the SEC sued Maske Thursday for fraud , saying its tweeting of August 7 misled investors .
Twitter said he was considering privatizing Tesla for $ 420 a share and had secured financing .
according to SEC , the tweets are actually groundless , and the market turmoil they have triggered has hurt investors .
investors and corporate governance experts say the deal could strengthen Tesla , which has been hard hit by Masque &apos;s recent behavior .
Steven Heim , head of asset management at Boston Comon , said the settlement should lead to more scrutiny of Maske and did not take &quot; destructive &quot; steps to drive him out of Tesla .
the asset management company owns shares in Panasonic , Tesla &apos;s battery maker .
under the proposed agreement , Tesla would have to appoint an independent chairman , two independent directors and a board of directors to set up controls over Masque &apos;s external communications .
&quot; it is in the best interest of our markets and our investors , including Tesla shareholders , that the matter be settled quickly on the agreed terms , &quot; SEC Chairman Clayton said in a statement .
Thursday &apos;s charges led to the evaporation of about $ 7 billion in the market value of Tesla , which stood at $ 45.2 billion at Friday , down from $ 47.5 billion at General Motors .
the SEC withdrew its claim in the settlement agreement to oust Maske from the helm of the company .
many investors say the punishment would be disastrous .
&quot; I think this is the best possible outcome for all concerned , &quot; said Ivan Feinseth of Tigrity Financial Partners , who gave Tesla a &quot; neutral &quot; rating and called the SEC &apos;s punishment &quot; light punishment &quot; for Masque .
&quot; it &apos;s important for Tesla that he remains CEO . &quot;
neither Musk nor Tesla acknowledged or denied the SEC &apos;s allegations in the settlement agreement and did not immediately respond to the request for comment .
the settlement agreement still needs to be approved by the court .
