Shanghai , Sept . 30 - China Securities Regulatory Commission ( CSRC ) on Sunday officially issued revised &quot; Guidelines for the Governance of Listed Companies , &quot; which focus on further tightening restrictions on controlling shareholders , actual controllers and their related parties , paying more attention to the protection of small and medium @-@ sized investors and giving play to the role of institutions for the protection of small and medium @-@ sized investors , while actively drawing on international experience to promote the participation of institutional investors in corporate governance .
the securities regulatory commission pointed out that the revised guidelines cover the basic concepts and principles for the management of listed companies , the composition and operation of shareholders ' meetings , boards of directors , and boards of supervisors , the rights and obligations of directors , supervisors , and senior managers , the incentive and restraint mechanism for listed companies , and the standards of conduct for controlling shareholders and their affiliated parties .
the new guidelines also cover the participation of institutional investors and relevant institutions in corporate governance , the basic requirements of listed companies in terms of stakeholders , environmental protection and social responsibility , and information disclosure and transparency .
the revised guidelines require listed companies to implement innovative , coordinated , green , open and shared development concepts in corporate governance , increase the requirements for party building of listed companies , and strengthen the leading role of listed companies in environmental protection and social responsibility .
strengthen the role of the Board of Directors Audit Committee and establish a basic framework for environmental , social responsibility and corporate governance ( ESG ) disclosure .
in addition , in response to various concerns , the new guidelines also set new requirements for the stability of control in the governance of listed companies , the performance of independent directors , the evaluation and incentive and restraint mechanism of the listed company , and the strengthening of information disclosure .
the securities regulatory commission also pointed out that in accordance with the new guidelines , it will study and perfect relevant regulations , normative documents , and guide the stock exchanges , the china association of listed companies , and other self-regulatory organizations to formulate and revise relevant self-regulatory rules and gradually improve the system of rules governing listed companies .
at the same time , we should strengthen the training of listed companies , strengthen the consciousness of improving the management and standardizing the operation of listed companies , and constantly improve the quality of listed companies .
Chinese President Xi Jinping said Monday that China &apos;s doors will not be closed until they are wider and higher , and that the pace of pushing for higher levels of openness will not stop .
expanding imports is not an equity measure , but a long @-@ term consideration for the future , with imports of goods and services expected to exceed $ 30 trillion and $ 10 trillion , respectively , over the next 15 years .
in his keynote speech at the first china international import expo , Xi Jinping said : China will further reduce tariffs , speed up the development of new industries such as cross - border electric merchants , continue to relax market access , promote the opening up of service industries , and relax restrictions on the ratio of foreign capital to shares in education , medical , and other fields where the domestic market has a large gap .
China will protect the legitimate rights and interests of foreign - funded enterprises .
he said : China will pay close attention to studying and putting forward Hainan 's policy and system of building a free trade port in stages to speed up the process of exploring and building a free trade port with chinese characteristics . a new section of the Shanghai free trade zone will be added . a science and technology innovation board will be set up on the Shanghai stock exchange , and a registration system will be set up on a trial basis to support the development of regional integration in the chang Jiang delta and will be upgraded into a national strategy .
&quot; China &apos;s economy is a sea , not a small pond .
&quot; there are times when the wind is calm and there are times when there is a storm , &quot; Xi said . &quot; the storm can overturn small ponds , but not the sea .
after countless storms , the sea is still there !
after more than 5,000 years of hardship , China is still there !
facing the future , china will always be here ! "
he pointed out : economic globalization has suffered setbacks , multilateralism and a free trade system have been hit by many factors of instability , and the risks and challenges have increased . opening up and cooperation are an important driving force for strengthening international economic and trade cooperation . all countries should persist in opening up and integration , expand the space for mutually beneficial development , and strengthen macroeconomic coordination .
he stressed again that china will not close its doors , but will only open wider and wider , and the pace of pushing for a higher level of opening will not stop .
China will stimulate its import potential , conform to the trend of upgrading domestic consumption , adopt more active and effective measures , promote the increase of residents ' incomes , and cultivate middle and high - end consumption growth points .
China will respect international business practices and treat all types of enterprises registered in China on an equal footing .
China will protect the legitimate rights and interests of foreign @-@ funded enterprises , resolutely punish violations of the legitimate rights and interests of foreign businesses , especially intellectual property rights , improve the quality of intellectual property rights examination and examination efficiency , introduce a punitive compensation system , and significantly increase the cost of violating the law .
