Indonesian earthquake and tsunami deaths rise to 420 , with no casualties among Chinese citizens reported
the death toll from the powerful earthquake and tsunami in Indonesia &apos;s central Sulawesi province has risen to 420 , the official news agency Antala news agency said at midnight local time , citing figures released by Wilem Rampangilei , head of the country &apos;s disaster relief agency .
the official said that this was only statistics for the city of Palu , the capital of central Sulawesi province , excluding Dungala district , where the epicenter of the earthquake was located , and the nearby Sigi district , where communications were still suspended and no casualties had been reported .
as many roads in Palu city were severely damaged , heavy machinery was difficult to access , and the search and rescue work was very difficult .
to ensure rescue , the airport of Palu , which was closed on the evening of the 28 th , was reopened on the night of the 29 th and all commercial flights were suspended . the reporter had already arranged the boarding pass for the flight from Jakarta to Palu that evening and the flight was cancelled .
after the earthquake and tsunami , the chinese embassy in indonesia used various channels to investigate and verify the situation of chinese citizens in the disaster areas .
to date , no casualties among Chinese citizens have been reported .
