General secretary Xi Jinping delivered a very important speech at the forum for private enterprises , injecting firm confidence into the private economy as it moves toward a broader stage .
General secretary Xi Jinping emphasized that " letting entrepreneurs get rid of their ideological burdens and move forward lightly " has aroused strong resonance among the broad masses of entrepreneurs and innovative entrepreneurs .
market dynamism comes from people , especially entrepreneurs , and from entrepreneurship .
in the magnificent course of reform and opening up over the past 40 years , there have been tens of thousands of stories of entrepreneurs starting up and innovating , and the growth and growth of the entrepreneur group has constantly pushed forward china 's economic breakthroughs .
for some time now , some people in society have made some negative and suspicious remarks about the private economy .
the so - called " theory on the departure of the private economy " and the " new theory on public - private joint ventures " have aroused some entrepreneurs ' doubts and worries .
recently , some private enterprises have encountered many difficulties and problems in their operation and development .
for example , changes in the international economic environment have had an impact on some exporting enterprises ; rapid adjustments in the demand structure have led to transformative and escalating pressures ; and some policies have been uncoordinated , with policy effects overlapping or working in simple ways that have led to the opposite effect for some initially well @-@ intentioned policies , among others .
various factors are intertwined , the private economy is facing difficulties , some private enterprises are facing difficulties in their operations , and entrepreneurs have shown a lot of anxiety .
against this background , correcting erroneous understanding , removing the ideological burden of entrepreneurs , and letting enterprises concentrate on development are of particular practical significance . the government 's single - mindedness in promoting development has a bearing on market confidence and development expectations .
the forum again emphasized the important thesis of " three unchanged " : " the position and role of the non-public economy in china 's economic and social development have not changed ! "
in recent years , the party central committee has attached unprecedented importance to and provided institutional support for entrepreneurs , from profoundly promoting decentralization and establishing a power list system to creating an environment of rule of law that protects their legitimate rights and interests , creating a market environment of fair competition , and creating an atmosphere of respect for entrepreneurs throughout society .
the forum specifically proposed policies and measures to support the development and growth of private enterprises in six aspects , and launched a series of practical actions to work for the " light advance " of private enterprises .
all this has greatly encouraged the entrepreneur community and given more expectation to all sectors of society .
the key lies in putting the fog out of the way and putting the guidelines in place .
it is necessary to constantly create a better environment for the development of the private economy , help private enterprises solve difficulties in their development , and help them realize china 's economic restructuring and upgrading . it is necessary to let entrepreneurs feel fair in the market competition , feel safe in their legitimate operations , feel respect in social life , and stimulate innovative vigor and creative potential .
China 's economy has entered the process of moving toward high - quality development , requiring more entrepreneurs to display their aspirations , and providing more room and stage for entrepreneurs to develop their creativity .
we have reason to believe that with the further deepening of reform and the removal of obstacles , the private economy will usher in better development prospects and opportunities and move toward a broader stage .
China @-@ Singapore Network Realizes Online Verification of 46 Control Certificates in Inner Mongolia Import and Export Links
hhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhot , 5 Nov ( Xinhua ) -- the hhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhhh
Inner Mongolia enterprises can use paperless means to declare relevant documents to the customs , avoiding the previous on @-@ site travel , paper applications , repeated submission and so on .
it has been learned that document preparation time refers to the preparation time for all kinds of documents required for the import and export links prior to customs declaration , and is a major factor affecting the overall customs clearance time . to reduce the customs clearance time and reduce the customs clearance cost , it is necessary to reduce the documents .
prior to this , there were 86 kinds of supervision documents that needed customs examination in the import and export links , involving 19 departments .
it has been learned that in accordance with the principle of " cancelling mergers and mergers and withdrawing from examination at ports " and relying on the " single window " platform for international trade , the customs and excise department has docked with the systems of 16 other license - issuing organs and interlinked data , thus realizing the goal of running more data and fewer enterprises running errands .
according to the customs , in the past , enterprises had to return to and from the relevant departments ' on - site offices to submit paper applications , and the process was long and the auditing status could not be tracked in real time .
enterprise users can now directly log on to the Single Window portal for online applications .
after the examination and approval of the issuing department , the certificate electronic data will be transmitted to the customs , and the customs declaration data will be automatically matched with the customs declaration data at the customs clearance stage . the results of the examination and verification will be reported to the enterprises through the " single window " in a unified way , and the entire process of supervising the declaration , examination , customs clearance , and feedback of documents will be handled online .
Han Ginseng chicken soup exports to china up 20 - fold in 4 years or related to the increase in empty nest youths - china - Singapore net
analysis of 20 @-@ fold increase in export of Han Ginseng chicken soup to China in 4 years : related to the increase of empty nest youth
South Korea &apos;s ginseng broth exports more than $ 100,000 to China last year , up about 20 times from 2013 , the South Korean news agency reported on Friday .
according to the analysis , this increase is related to the increase in the number of empty nesting youth in china leading to the hot sale of convenience food , and the increase in the attention paid by young people to nutritious food .
the figures were released by the korea agricultural and aquatic food circulation commune ( aT ) on the 5 th .
South Korean ginseng chicken soup exported $ 100.339 million to china last year , weighing 218.59 million kg , up 209.4 percent and 3,668.8 percent , respectively , over 2013 .
according to the analysis , the increase in the sale of ginseng chicken soup in south korea is related to the increase in the number of empty - nest youths leading to the hot selling of convenience food , and the increase in the interest of young people in nutritious food .
as of this year , one @-@ person households in China have surpassed the 200 million mark and are expected to rise to 30 per cent of the total population by 2020 , with local food companies targeting &quot; sole proprietors &quot; to launch various convenience foods .
in addition , the analysis also said that bird flu is the biggest factor preventing ginseng chicken soup from taking root in the chinese mainland market .
a t said that the bird flu epidemic in south korea between november 2016 and april last year led to a sharp drop in exports due to a comprehensive ban on the export of ginseng chicken soup to china .
Ginseng chicken soup exported $ 840,000 to China in 2016 , and exports plunged to $ 100,000 last year as a result of bird flu .
