on the evening of 29 september , the reporter learned from the propaganda department of the qingbaijiang district CPC committee in Chengdu : on the evening of 29 september beijing time , a central european class ( Chengdu ) loaded with automotive connectors , telescopes , and liquid crystal display screens passed through the Semianovka port in Poland to exchange , transfer , and finally arrived at Nuremberg , Germany .
this is the first time that china and central europe have opened the Semianovka port line in Poland , marking the successful opening of another european transport line after mara and Jop in central europe .
the china - eu flight started at Chengdu 's qingbaijiang city box station on 14 september . it left the country through the Alaska pass and entered europe through the Semianovka port in Poland . it eventually arrived at Nuremberg , Germany , for a total of about 16 days .
this is the first time that china and europe have changed trains for broad and standard tracks .
the opening of this port has effectively solved the long - term operation and long - term problems caused by the current congestion at the Malay port , raised the time limit for the transportation of the liner , provided a new solution to the congestion problem at the Malay port , further improved the transportation capacity and efficiency of the hinterland in western china to the european mediterranean market , and laid a solid foundation for the development of the sino - european lineup of the european market .
more than 400 people have been confirmed dead in a 7.5 @-@ magnitude earthquake Friday in the Indonesian island of Sulawesi , many of them swept away by the tsunami caused by the quake .
authorities expect the total number of deaths on Sunday to rise sharply as new data are reported from remote areas .
dozens of people are reportedly still trapped under the ruins of a hotel and a shopping mall in Baru .
the city of Baru was hit by waves as high as six meters ( 20 feet ) high .
so far , only the death toll from Baru has been reported , and the death toll in Dungra , north of Baru , has been slow , and the authorities are preparing for a worse situation .
Dungera , with a population of 300,000 , is closer to the epicenter of the earthquake .
Indonesian Vice President Kara says the total number of deaths could rise to thousands .
hundreds of people gathered on the beach to celebrate the holiday when the huge waves hit the shore at nightfall on Friday . many were washed away and everything was ruined wherever they went .
Tokyo ( Reuters ) - The confidence of Japan &apos;s biggest manufacturers hit its lowest level in more than a year in the September quarter , according to a quarterly survey released Monday by the Bank of Japan , as companies felt pressure from rising raw @-@ material costs and a series of natural disasters that affected production .
the survey shows little evidence that escalating global trade frictions are dampening the confidence of large manufacturers .
but the risk of a full @-@ blown trade war has hit business prospects and could threaten corporate capital spending .
active capital spending is a bright spot in Japan &apos;s economy .
the survey raises questions about the Bank of Japan &apos;s view that robust economic expansion will help accelerate inflation to the 2 % target , despite signs that companies are shifting costs to customers .
&quot; with the global trade war causing concern , manufacturers &apos; confidence is stagnating as exports slow and factory production weakens , &quot; said Nan Wushi , chief researcher at the Golden Complex Institute in Agriculture and Forestry .
&quot; confidence is still high , and because corporate profits are improving and prices are rising , I don &apos;t think confidence will continue to fall , &quot; he said .
a short survey showed that in september , the index of judging of the large manufacturing economy dropped from a positive 21 three months ago to a positive 19 , worsening for the third consecutive quarter .
the median market estimate is positive 22 .
for the first time in eight quarters , the Large Non @-@ Manufacturing Competitiveness Index fell to 22.0 in September from 24.0 in June .
Reuters survey was positive 22 .
the survey showed that the average of the indices for both large manufacturing and non - manufacturing sectors remained stable in december .
the Nikkei Nikkei Nikkei rose Monday to a 27 @-@ year high as the continued depreciation of the yen helped improve the export earnings prospects of Japanese companies .
capital spending is robust .
despite the decline in business confidence , the latest short @-@ term outlook highlights the robustness of corporate capital spending plans , thanks to renewed capacity and increased investment in robotics and automation to cope with labor shortages caused by an ageing population .
a short @-@ term survey by the central bank shows that large companies plan to increase their capital spending by 13.4 % for the fiscal year ending March 2019 .
this compares with 13.6 per cent in the previous short @-@ term survey .
Mr Namuchi said all corporate capital spending plans were growing by 8.5 per cent this fiscal year , close to the pace of Japan &apos;s bubble @-@ economy era .
&quot; there is room for further growth in capital spending in the light of higher profit forecasts for small businesses from now on , but much depends on the impact of the trade war on business confidence , &quot; he said .
the short @-@ term survey , which showed an increase in the ability of firms to pass on costs , and the positive 7 of the large enterprise output price index , the highest in a decade , are encouraging signs of progress in Japan &apos;s efforts to counter deflation .
the index measuring employment in large enterprises reached minus 23 , the highest level since 1992 , highlighting the tightening of the labour market .
benefiting from strong corporate spending , Japan &apos;s economy rebounded in the second quarter from the January @-@ March contraction .
but the prospect of Japan &apos;s export @-@ dependent economy is overshadowed by rising trade frictions and natural @-@ disaster disruptions to the supply chain in the summer .
in dollar terms , exports and imports of services grew by 16.4 per cent .
in January @-@ August , imports and exports of emerging services surpassed $ 1 trillion , growing faster than overall , according to a spokesman for the Department of Trade and Industry , quoted in a press release on the Ministry of Commerce website .
of this , the total value of imports and exports of new services was 1.138 trillion yuan , up 20.9 percent , 10.4 percentage points higher than the overall growth rate of imports and exports of services , and nearly 3 percentage points higher than that of new services .
in terms of services exports , from january to august , service exports continued the rapid growth momentum since the beginning of this year , with exports growing at 5.7 percentage points faster than imports .
the top three areas of growth were telecommunications computers and information services , personal cultural and entertainment services , and insurance services , with growth rates of 61.1 percent , 38.8 percent and 26.5 percent , respectively .
the head of the department also pointed out that the proportion of imports of new services also gradually increased from january to august .
from january to august , imports of new services grew rapidly , accounting for 23.6 percent of imports of services , up 1.6 percentage points over the same period last year .
among them , imports of financial services , intellectual property rights , telecommunications computers , and information services all grew by over 20 percent , at 47.1 percent , 23.3 percent , and 23.2 percent , respectively .
