oil prices or ushered in the &quot; three consecutive rises &quot; national day self @-@ driving travel can be filled ahead of time .
chinanews , beijing , september 30 ( reporter Qiu yu ) at 2400 hours on september 30 , a new round of price adjustment window for refined oil products will be opened simultaneously with the national day holiday .
many organizations predict that oil prices will rise sharply to realize the " three consecutive increases . "
car owners who plan to drive by themselves can fill up their cars with fuel before prices rise .
according to the data from the rummage information measurement , it is expected that the corresponding increase in domestic refined oil output will be about 190 yuan per ton , and that of Zhuo chong information measurement will be about 220 yuan per ton .
in September , oil prices had been revised upwards twice : on 3 September , gasoline was moved upwards by 180 yuan / ton , diesel by 170 yuan / ton , and on 17 September , gasoline was moved upwards by 145 yuan / ton and diesel oil was moved upwards by 145 yuan / ton .
domestic oil prices are linked to international oil prices , which have risen since the current price cycle , and Brent crude oil has gone beyond the $ 80 threshold and continued to probe .
the U.S. WTI crude closed at $ 1.13 at $ 73.25 a barrel as of Sept . 28 .
Brent crude oil futures closed up $ 1.0 at $ 82.72 a barrel .
" judging from the international situation , the united states ' sanctions against iran and other tense sentiments have multiplied , and the overall trend of oil prices has been rather strong . subsequently , the OPEC production reduction meeting explicitly refused to increase production , gave market confidence , and steadily moved oil prices up . "
Zhuo Chuang information products analyst Zang Wengang said .
on the retail side , the current petrol prices at CNPC and Sinopec gas stations are 7.66 yuan per litre and 8.15 yuan per litre , respectively .
according to li Yan , a leading information analyst , there has not been much change in the retail sales strategy of petrol stations . at present , the concessions at major stations , such as Sinopec , range from 0.5 yuan to 0.7 yuan per litre , while the concessions at private gas stations range from 0.5 yuan to 1.2 yuan per litre .
&quot; the retail price is about to rise &quot; three times , &quot; or about 0.14 @-@ 0.16 yuan , suggesting that owners of private cars fill up with oil before the National Day holiday , &quot; Li said .
