69th International Astronautical Congress opens in Germany - China @-@ Singapore Network
Xinhua news agency , Bremen , Germany , october 1 ( reporter ren yirong ) the 69th international aerospace congress opened on october 1 at the Bremen convention and exhibition center in Germany , attended by more than 6,300 astronauts , representatives of space agencies and enterprises , experts , scholars , and young students from all over the world .
speaking at the opening ceremony , Jean @-@ Yves Logar , President of the International Astronautical Federation , said that the global space industry was no longer a small number of countries and institutions , and that the number of participants had increased significantly since the previous session , indicating that more and more institutions and individuals were joining in .
he called on all countries to strengthen cooperation and innovation and jointly promote the development of the space industry .
Zhang kejian , vice minister of china 's ministry of industry and information technology and director of the state space administration , briefed the guests on china 's space program , saying that china will expand international cooperation in the field of aerospace and make contributions to mankind 's space undertakings .
representatives of the china aerospace science and technology corporation , the china aerospace science and technology corporation , and other relevant organizations , as well as some private enterprises , attended the meeting and showed the latest achievements of china 's aerospace industry , including various types of carrier rockets , satellites , and aerospace science and technology application products .
the International Astronautical Congress , which has been held annually since 1950 , is the largest gathering in the world aviation community .
the five @-@ day Congress was co @-@ sponsored by the International Astronautical Federation , the International Academy of Astronautics , the Centre for Applied Science , Technology and Microgravity Studies of Bremen University and the International Institute of Space Law .
Beijing ( Reuters ) - China &apos;s foreign trade situation remains complex and grim , with 80.6 per cent of companies expecting exports in 2018 to be better or flat all year round , according to a press release issued Sunday by the China Foreign Trade Center .
however , in view of the external environment in which the cost of domestic raw materials , labor , and other comprehensive factors continue to rise and the impact of sino - us trade frictions is increasing , the exhibitors also hold that next year 's export situation is not optimistic .
at the closing news conference of the 124th Guangzhou trade fair , Xu bing , deputy secretary general and press spokesman of the Guangzhou trade fair and deputy director of the china foreign trade center , said that the number of overseas buyers attending the trade fair and the volume of export transactions were down slightly from the same period last year .
the number of buyers attending the session , 189,812 from 215 countries and territories , decreased by 1.11 per cent year @-@ on @-@ year .
export transactions amounted to 206.494 billion yuan ( US $ 29.86 billion ) , a decrease of 1 per cent over the same period last year .
judging from the market , transactions in japan , the 10 ASEAN countries , the " BRIC " countries , and the rok grew by 74.4 percent , 11.4 percent , 7.2 percent , and 2.5 percent respectively , and in the traditional markets of the united states , australia , canada , and the european union , respectively , they fell by 30.3 percent , 8.9 percent , 7.3 percent , and 0.8 percent .
in terms of industry , transport vehicles , machinery and equipment , construction and decoration materials , consumer electronics and information products , and sanitary appliances grew by 24.8 percent , 21.1 percent , 20.0 percent , 15.1 percent and 7.6 percent respectively , while textiles , clothing , and household electrical appliances decreased by 13.0 percent and 6.7 percent respectively .
Xu bing said : as a barometer and a weathervane for china 's foreign trade , the participation of buyers at the current Guangzhou trade fair and the data on export transactions show that china 's foreign trade development will still face many uncertain factors next year .
however , with the deepening of the supply - side structural reform and the recent introduction of policies and measures in the areas of " six stability " by the state and localities , china 's new dynamic for foreign trade development is rapidly accumulating , and new progress has been made in the diversification of the enterprise market . these are all important bases and powerful conditions for the development of foreign trade .
" taking all relevant factors into account , it is expected that china 's foreign trade imports and exports will maintain steady growth throughout the year , and the quality and efficiency will be further enhanced , " Xu bing said .
China &apos;s General Administration of Customs announced that exports rose 14.5 per cent year @-@ on @-@ year in dollar terms in September , while imports grew 14.3 per cent year @-@ on @-@ year , with a trade surplus of $ 31.69 billion in September , and both the export growth rate and the trade surplus were the highest since February .
despite escalating trade frictions between china and the united states , china 's export performance in september was still much higher than expected , and foreign demand was strong , and enterprises ' scrambling to export the superimposed RMB exchange rate before the united states imposed tariffs , or the main supporting factors , also showed a certain degree of toughness in china 's foreign trade . however , the impact of the sino - us trade war on confidence and on the industrial chain cannot be underestimated . analysts believe that china 's foreign trade challenges may appear in the fourth quarter or next year .
U.S. fund managers suggested in September to increase cash holdings and remain cautious as the United States and China began the latest round of mutual import tariffs and the dispute showed no signs of abating , Reuters said .
but North America &apos;s asset allocation has risen to its highest level since June 2017 , and positions in the UK , the eurozone , and especially emerging markets have fallen , according to 12 fund managers who participated in the survey .
global equities averaged 56.6 per cent and bonds 35.5 per cent , largely in line with last month &apos;s survey .
the most significant change was the rise in the cash ratio to 5.1 per cent , the highest level since December 2014 .
&quot; some economic data bring confidence to the market , but the trade war is still the biggest concern , so it &apos;s better to be prepared to enter if the market falls , &quot; said a fund manager at a large fund company .
but fund managers preferred stocks in September , especially in the United States , even though American stocks were considered too expensive .
