Zhao leqin , secretary of the Guilin city CPC committee , said : after the new terminal is opened , it will be able to meet the demand for 12 million passengers per year and build up a new advantage in Guilin 's air traffic . it will be of great significance to further improve the modern three - dimensional traffic pattern of Guangxi 's Jiang - sea joint movement , sea - rail combined transport , water - land transport , and air - port links .
Guilin is expected to receive more than 90 million visitors this year .
the T2 Terminal of Guilin and Jiangjiang International Airport and its supporting facilities expansion project is a major public welfare project marking the 60th anniversary of the establishment of the Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region , as well as a landmark project for the construction of Guilin International Tourism Resort .
the project began construction in December 2015 , with a gross floor area of 100,000 square metres and a total investment of 3,258 million yuan . after the project is completed and put into operation , it will be able to meet the needs of 12 million passengers per year , 101,200 sorties and 95,000 tons of cargo and mail throughput .
on the same day , more than 200 flights took off and landed at Terminal T2 of Guilin Two Rivers International Airport .
inspired by the landscape of Guilin , the design of the new terminal building looks like a " mountain and water laurel crown , " with a close view of the " dragon ridge terraced fields " and the superimposed eaves of the residential buildings in northern Guilin , which intersect with the landscape of Guilin .
it has been learned that the new terminal building at Guilin airport can meet the peak traffic of nearly 4,000 passengers per hour , and has used " intelligent baggage sorting system , security integration platform , face recognition , " and other " smart airport " technical means to plan a commercial district covering various types of business activities , such as catering , 100 goods , tax exemption , and leisure and entertainment .
