on 29 september , china 's first 3000 - ton large buoy ship " xiangyang hong 22 " landed in the chinese armed ships group .
when completed , the ship will break the current equipment bottlenecks in china 's support work , such as large - scale buoys , submarine deployment , recovery , and emergency repairs .
the " xiangyang red 22 " is mainly used to provide support for the regular inspection and maintenance of buoys / submarines , regular deployment , recovery , emergency deployment of buoys / submarines , recovery , emergency repair , and so on . at the same time , it has the capability to carry out comprehensive marine survey missions such as cross - section survey .
the new ship has a total length of 89 metres , a width of 18 metres and a depth of 7.2 metres , and a capacity of 10,000 nautical miles .
Wang weiling , deputy general manager of the armed ships group , said : " Xiangyang hong 22 is china 's first large - scale buoy operation ship , and is also the only domestic large - scale buoy operation vessel with the ability to hoist 10 meters , which will further enhance china 's large - scale buoy support capability . "
it has been learned that the ship will be put into use by the east china sea subbureau of the state oceanic administration . Chen qiu , director of the observation department of the marine early warning and monitoring department of the ministry of natural resources of china , said that the ship 's commissioning will be of great significance to the development of china 's offshore ocean observation system and the promotion of global ocean observation .
" this ship has both large - scale buoy deployment and maintenance operations , as well as comprehensive marine survey capability . it is china 's first comprehensive ship dedicated to the operation of buoys and comprehensive marine surveys in the middle and distant seas .
with such buoy ships , our ocean observations and oceanographic surveys will have powerful tools in the future . "
