affected by typhoon " tam Mei , " strong winds kept blowing in the harbor , and the maximum wind speed was as high as 24 knots . the departure signal was delayed by nearly 90 minutes from 1 : 00 p.m . on the 30 th . , but the wind speed remained unchanged . the referee - in - chief Anne mdrant announced that the first day of the competition would be cancelled and the game postponed until the afternoon of 1 october .
&quot; the strong winds from the shore keep blowing , and the sea is too rough . &quot;
&quot; under such circumstances , no one knows when a gust of wind is blowing towards the racing ship , &quot; Mudrand explained .
close to the city &apos;s court , cancellation is the wisest option in the current situation .
all the crew who were ready were still somewhat disappointed .
&quot; the race ship is ready to stop , and we are in good shape . &quot;
