despite the continued turmoil in global financial markets , the hong kong monetary authority said on Monday that the exchange fund 's investment income in the third quarter of this year was down by 97% year - on - year , but better than in the previous quarter , as foreign exchange losses narrowed markedly as overseas stocks rose amid the sino - us trade war .
according to the latest HKMA data , investment income of HK $ 1.6 billion was recorded by the exchange fund in july - september 2018 , down significantly from HK $ 61.8 billion in the same period last year , but up from the revised HK $ 100 million in the second quarter of this year .
speaking at the legislative council , chief executive of the HKMA , mr chan tak - lam , said that the hong kong and emerging markets stock indices were at odds with the us stock indices in the early days of the sino - us trade war . by the end of september and early october , after the us stock market indices had peaked , market sentiment began to reverse as investors gradually realized that the trade war was also detrimental to the united states itself .
&quot; a change in market sentiment is good , and it won &apos;t help much if the trade war has only a one @-@ sided effect . &quot;
but he also pointed out : " if the sino - us trade war is not resolved , financial market volatility will continue to rise . "
in the third quarter of this year , the exchange fund 's losses on equity investments in hong kong narrowed by 8% over the previous quarter to HK $ 4.7 billion , while gains on overseas equity investments soared by 172% to HK $ 12.8 billion , while foreign exchange losses of HK $ 16.2 billion and bond yields of HK $ 9.7 billion decreased by 24% and 31% respectively , mainly reflecting the general rise in the us dollar against major currencies during the quarter and the 3.0% rise in us interest rates in mid - september .
the exchange fund mainly supports the hong kong dollar .
Hong kong has been implementing a pegged exchange rate system for the hong kong dollar to the us dollar since 1983 .
with regard to hong kong 's current financial situation , Chen Delin said that economic and asset market uncertainty had increased and downside risks had increased , but hong kong 's financial system was robust , and it was also well prepared to withstand earthquakes .
&quot; Hong Kong has a strong international investment position , with a net external asset value of $ 1.4 trillion equivalent to four times GDP , 2.5 times that of Singapore and 0.6 times that of Japan , and more than enough to cope with the downturn or reversal of the economy . &quot;
noting that the hong kong dollar exchange rate had risen by more than 400 basis points on september 21 , mr chan pointed out that the hong kong dollar was widely believed to be mainly related to the rise in hong kong dollar interest rates . the hong kong dollar had since hovered around 7.80 - 7.84 . the recent continued fall in hong kong dollar interest rates and the widening of the interest rate spread with the us dollar were likely to attract the market to sell hong kong dollars and buy us dollars , making the hong kong dollar more likely to trigger another weak party 's convertibility guarantee .
however , he believes that with the start of the interest rate hike cycle for banks in hong kong and the normalization of hong kong dollar interest rates , the situation where hong kong dollar interest rates are lower than us dollar rates will change in the future .
&quot; Hong Kong dollar interest rates will converge more closely with those of the US dollar . we need to manage risk more carefully and be prepared to cope with market fluctuations . &quot;
as hong kong dollar funds were abundant , hong kong dollar interest rates fell further , dropping 0.9% to 2.08179% on Monday from 46 basis points to 51 basis points against the us dollar , while the one - month interest rate spread reached a five - month low , expanding from 120 basis points to 127 basis points against the us dollar .
from May to mid @-@ September , the spot Hong Kong dollar exchange rate was close to 7.85 to US $ 1 for most of the period .
during the period , the weak party convertibility bonds were triggered in may and august , after being triggered for the first time in april , due to such factors as the outflow of some of the funds from the offering after the completion of the hedging activities and the large - scale offering activities .
under the linked exchange rate system , the HKMA buys hong kong dollars at 7.85 and sells us dollars to maintain the stability of the hong kong dollar exchange rate .
the HKMA purchased about HK $ 52.1 billion under the weak party convertibility undertaking mechanism in may and august .
is the new tax law more favorable to people from outside the country ?
in response to a reporter 's question on the 30 th , a responsible person of the ministry of finance and the state administration of taxation said that in order to maintain policy stability , when implementing the new personal income tax law , consideration will be given to continuing to make preferential arrangements for people from outside the country , including those from hong kong , Macao , and Taiwan .
a reporter asked : the newly revised personal income tax law has revised the criteria for judging individual income tax residents in china from one year to more than 183 days .
will there be any preferential arrangements for overseas people , including those from hong kong , Macao and Taiwan , when the law is next implemented ?
the responsible person replied that the current regulations on the implementation of the personal income tax law have special preferential provisions for tax payment by persons outside china . individuals who have no domicile in china but who have resided for more than one year and less than five years may pay personal income tax only for part of the income they receive from units or individuals inside china .
the responsible person said that in order to maintain policy stability , the next step in implementing the new personal income tax law would be to continue to make preferential arrangements for people from outside the country , including those from hong kong , Macao and Taiwan .
there is no &quot; threshold &quot; of moonlight center : quality certification to promote quality .
with the development of the " two - child economy , " and the prosperity of the mother and child market , from the north to the third and fourth - tier cities , various types of monthly clubs have sprung up in various localities .
the burning moonlight clubs have met the masses ' consumption needs , charging fees ranging from tens of thousands to hundreds of thousands of yuan , but at the same time they are in an awkward situation . the organization has so far no thresholds and there is still a gap in supervision .
the state general administration of market supervision recently launched a series of national " quality month " activities in 2018 , with reporters visiting a five - star moon center in Tianjin to see the experience of certification of mother and child care services .
General moonlight centers provide neonatal care , nutritional meals , postpartum repair and plastic services .
in this month 's children 's center , the reporter saw that nurses check the breastfeeding status of newborn babies every day , and professional nurses provide the newborn with fine care services such as bathing and touching .
at the same time , to meet the needs of new mothers , services ranging from wound care in the early months of the moon to beauty care in the middle and late months of the month , provide traditional Chinese medicine treatment and beauty care programs to help mothers regain their sexual appearance .
a new mother living in the house told reporters that she had booked up to eight months in advance .
the services provided by the moonlight clubs have a direct impact on the comfort and physical recovery of the mothers during the month . some small @-@ scale moonlight clubs can only provide some simple moonlight services . there are hidden dangers such as disinfection , unruly hygiene , easy cross @-@ infection , and unscientific diet .
the head of the moonlight center said they were the only five @-@ star moonlight center in Tianjin to be certified as having a B @-@ level service .
&quot; while some customers do not understand the meaning of Level B certification at first , it is important for the long @-@ term development of an enterprise to benefit from a strict standardized process management through certification , &quot; he said .
Pan liefen , deputy director general of the certification and supervision department of the state general administration of market supervision , said : service certification is a new type of certification system based on customer perception , concern for organizational quality management , and satisfaction of service characteristics . it is an important component of the state 's quality infrastructure and plays a positive role in raising the proportion of quality services provided and enhancing the international competitiveness of china 's services .
China began in 2004 . after more than 10 years of development , service certification projects have undergone a process of development from scratch . a number of influential service certifications have emerged , such as certification of financial services , certification of mother and child care services , certification of after - sale services for commodities , certification of e - commerce services , and certification of health services .
according to the statistics of the state general administration of market supervision and control , china currently has more than 130 service certification organizations , more than 2,000 service certifiers , and nearly 8,000 valid certification certificates .
Pan liefen said that it is necessary to further guide and promote the development of service certification , gradually expand service certification coverage in the areas of health , education , sports , finance , and electrical commerce , and promote supply - side reform and quality improvement in the service sector .
Hong KONG Nov 5 - Hong KONG &apos;s property prices have fallen for two months after peaking , Hong Kong Monetary Authority Chief Executive Donald Chan said on Monday that it would take time to see if the housing market is entering a downward cycle and , if confirmed , consider relaxing the tightening of countercyclical measures at an appropriate time .
Mr chan also pointed out that if property prices were to fall back , it would be the home buyers who would be the first to be affected during the peak period of the property market . however , it was expected that in the event of a sharp drop in property prices in the wake of the asian financial crisis in 1997 , the chances of a sharp reduction in property prices would be much lower .
speaking at the legislative council briefing led by mr chan tak - lam , mr chan said that if the housing market was confirmed to be in a downward cycle , the measures could be relaxed in due course .
&quot; however , it is still too early to relax as we see only a few weeks of data . we still need more time to see if the housing market is entering a downward cycle , &quot; he said .
since October 2009 , the HKMA has introduced eight rounds of counter @-@ cyclical measures to significantly tighten mortgages for various types of properties , including reducing mortgage yields and requiring mortgage applicants to pass rigorous stress tests , with a view to enhancing bank risk management and resilience to earthquakes .
as hong kong formally entered the interest rate hike cycle , the hong kong private residential property price index fell for the second consecutive month in august - september , and the monthly decline in september widened to 1.44% .
however , the cumulative increase in the first three quarters of this year remained at 10.2% .
according to HKMA data , the financial position of households measuring their resilience to financial risks in hong kong remained healthy , with 66 per cent of households living in private homes without mortgages in the second quarter of this year , up from an average of 60 per cent in 2009 - 11 , and 47 per cent and 34 per cent respectively in new mortgage approvals and new mortgage approvals , up significantly from 64 per cent and 41 per cent in 2009 - 11 .
however , mr chan said that the high earthquake resistance did not mean that homeowners would not be adversely affected by the economic downturn , as property valuations would fall and buyers would bear the brunt during the peak period .
although the HKMA has tightened banks ' lending to mortgage borrowers , homebuyers can also obtain a high percentage of mortgage loans through mortgage insurance or the provision of mortgage loans by developers .
Mr chan said that , together with the mortgage loans provided to developers , the loan - to - value ratio of borrowers could reach 85 - 90 per cent , and if the property price were to fall by 10 per cent , there would be negative assets ( i.e. the market value of the property would fall below the total outstanding mortgage loans ) .
however , mr Nguyen Kwok - Heng , deputy chief executive of the HKMA , pointed out that it was estimated that the percentage of the total amount of mortgages provided by developers would be only 2.5% to 2.5% , which was still relatively low .
at the peak of negative equity in hong kong in 2003 , the number of negative equity cases exceeded 100,000 , accounting for 22% of the supply .
as at the third quarter of this year , hong kong recorded zero negative assets for seven consecutive quarters .
Xinhua news agency , beijing , october 1 ( liu hongxia and ma Rui ) e - commerce retail export enterprises welcomed another wave of favorable taxes on october 1 , involving value - added tax and excise tax exemption .
a few days ago , the ministry of finance , the state administration of taxation , the ministry of commerce , and the general administration of customs jointly issued a written statement explicitly stating that the tax exemption policy for value - added tax and consumption tax should be implemented on an experimental basis if the export enterprises of electric merchants in the comprehensive experimental zone of cross - border electronic commerce export goods that do not have valid import certificates at the same time meet the following conditions .
first , e @-@ commerce export enterprises are registered in the comprehensive test area , and the date of export , name of goods , unit of measure , quantity , unit price and amount of goods are registered on the comprehensive service platform of the cross @-@ border e @-@ commerce line of the place of registration .
second , export goods go through the customs in the comprehensive test area to go through the electronic commerce export declaration formalities .
third , the export of goods does not belong to the Ministry of Finance and the General Administration of Taxation in accordance with the State Council &apos;s decision to explicitly eliminate export tax rebate ( exemption ) goods .
the circular clearly states that the General Administration of Customs regularly transmits electronic information from the electronic commerce export declaration list to the State Administration of Taxation .
the tax authorities of the comprehensive test zones shall strengthen the duty @-@ free administration of export goods in accordance with the electronic information contained in the export commodity declaration lists drawn up by the State Administration of Taxation .
the circular points out that the specific tax - free administrative measures shall be formulated by the provincial tax departments ' business , financial , and commercial departments .
the offices of the leading groups for the construction of comprehensive test zones and the departments in charge of commerce should make concerted efforts to promote communication and cooperation among the departments and the implementation of relevant policies , speed up the establishment of a statistical monitoring system for the export of electronic commerce , and promote the healthy and rapid development of cross - border electronic commerce .
