MOF waives VAT consumption tax on cross - border electric companies
the circular points out that if the export enterprises of e - commerce in the comprehensive test zone export goods that do not have valid import vouchers and meet the relevant conditions , the policies of tax exemption for value - added tax and consumption tax will be implemented on a trial basis .
( 1 ) E @-@ commerce exporting enterprises are registered in the comprehensive test area and the date of export , name of goods , unit of measurement , quantity , unit price and amount of goods are registered on the comprehensive service platform of the cross @-@ border e @-@ commerce line of the place of registration .
( 2 ) Export goods shall go through the customs at the place where the comprehensive test zone is located to go through the formalities of electronic commerce export declaration .
( 3 ) Exports of goods that do not belong to the Ministry of Finance and the General Administration of Taxation shall , in accordance with the decision of the State Council , expressly abolish the export tax rebate ( exemption ) .
it is understood that the above @-@ mentioned circular will take effect from 1 October 2018 , depending on the date of export indicated in the export declaration list .
fifth &quot; Disabled Voice Month &quot; Comes to Focus on Sex Education for Disabled Adolescents - China @-@ Singapore Network
in recent years , the topic of sex education for Chinese teenagers has been widely discussed , but the challenge for sex education for disabled teenagers remains daunting .
recently , a seminar on the challenges and practical strategies of comprehensive sexuality education for people with disabilities was held in Beijing .
how to provide sex education to disabled children and youth has become an important topic of this seminar .
the &quot; Report on Sexual Knowledge , Attitudes and Behaviour of Disabled Children and Young People in China &quot; released at the meeting showed that disabled children were more exposed to sexual harassment and sexual abuse than healthy children .
for disabled children , adolescents , and society , more attention is also given to &quot; sexual protection . &quot;
the seminar is aimed at promoting comprehensive sexuality education for disabled children and young people in China in terms of family support , school education and institutional services , and providing support at the source to disabled children and young people so that they can have the same right to enjoy love as others .
experts believe that all along , the Chinese public &apos;s understanding of the disabled has remained at a level that is not deep enough .
influenced by traditional attitudes and other factors , China &apos;s comprehensive sexuality education for people with disabilities , especially disabled children and adolescents , is not yet thorough enough .
however , in recent years , with the support of the unesco and the public interest , there have been gratifying developments in the practice and implementation path of comprehensive sexual and reproductive health education for the disabled throughout the cycle in china .
the Report shows that although children and young people with visual , hearing , intellectual and physical impairments have some more difficulty in acquiring sexual knowledge and understanding of intimate relationships than the general population , on the whole they have progressed toward convenience and richness .
sponsored by the Shanghai Foundation for the Public Interest , and supported by the UNESCO representative office in China , the International Disability Alliance ( France ) representative office in Beijing and the UNFPA representative office in China , the seminar aims to explore the practice and implementation path of comprehensive sexual and reproductive health education for persons with disabilities throughout the cycle , and to promote understanding among policymakers , educators , researchers , social service organizations , parents and other stakeholders in the field of special education , how to develop a blueprint for comprehensive sexuality education and for children and young people with disabilities .
Beijing , Sept . 30 ( Reuters ) - The central bank &apos;s short @-@ term foreign currency position against local currency forward contracts and futures contracts remained nil for 12 consecutive months at the end of August , according to figures released Sunday by the People &apos;s Bank of China on net projected short @-@ term outflows of foreign currency assets .
previous central bank data showed that by the end of August , the central bank held a total of $ 6,044 million in short positions in foreign currency against local currency forward and futures contracts , unchanged for the fourth month in a row , and a total of $ 4,276 million in short positions in SDR terms .
since then , the central bank &apos;s foreign @-@ exchange forward position has been nil .
the central bank released the data for the first time at the end of March 2016 ; the data showed that at the end of February 2016 , the central bank had a foreign currency position of $ 2,438 million against local currency forward and futures contracts , and a short position of $ 28.9 billion .
September data released at the end of October showed a net short @-@ term increase of $ 16,401 million to $ 45,301 million for the first time .
the central bank had previously said that the forward and short - term foreign currency positions mainly reflected the central bank 's forward foreign exchange operations with commercial banks to meet the hedging needs of enterprises ' foreign currency liabilities , and that it would continue to provide forward risk - averse products on the basis of actual demand . the central bank 's forward operations would have a smaller impact on the future foreign exchange reserve scale .
