one of the great men on the train bought a seat without a seat , but took her seat : &quot; shoot it . &quot;
after two hours of driving , the conductor advised him to remain invalid for an hour .
in the end , a male passenger in the same carriage couldn &apos;t look down on him and pulled him up .
judging from public opinion , although most of the end result is that the hegemonists are condemned by the public , punished administratively by the public security departments , and even blacklisted for honesty , the public still feels that they do not " dispel their hatred " : why should they not be punished on the spot ?
why not stop his immoral or even illegal behaviour on the spot and punish him afterwards ?
and how can the unreasonable behavior of the " hegemonic lord " be pulled up by only a male passenger who is " out of order " ?
the main reason for this is that only long - distance trains are equipped with police , and short - distance trains are generally not available ; even if they do , the police are more concerned about the possible rogue reaction of the hegemonists and do not take measures to force them to leave .
repeated bullying has made people realize that bullies must be forcibly removed and even punished on the spot in order to act as a deterrent .
this requires that our train passengers should dare to take strong and timely measures , and that those trains that do not carry police officers should be deployed as soon as possible in order to prevent and crack down on illegal activities in a timely manner .
