at about 13:00 , the Beichuan traffic police received a call for help , saying that his family had a traffic accident in songpan , and that due to the limited medical conditions in the area , he was in urgent need of medical treatment in Mianyang .
it happened to be a one @-@ way traffic control operation on Tangjiashan Yan lake ring road in Beichuan , and wanted to ask traffic police to release the 120 emergency vehicles .
upon receiving the call for help , the police on duty promptly reported the situation to the brigade . after Huang xuemin , commander of the brigade , made a brief understanding of the situation , he immediately arranged for the police on duty at the control point to contact the callers and asked them to make all - out efforts to provide escorts .
&quot; after contacting the 120 first aid vehicles , we expect to arrive in Beichuan at around 1500 hours . arrangements will be made immediately . &quot;
the squadron leader of the beichuan traffic police 's yu li squadron said that first aid vehicles needed to go around the jiashan Yan sehu roundabout road , and the roads were steep and narrow . in order to prevent vehicles that had already entered this section of the road from running in parallel , traffic police put vehicles under block control one hour ahead of schedule at three points , including the beginning , middle , and end of the road , and reminded all passing drivers to leave the side of the road to make way for emergency vehicles .
subsequently , the drumming squadron police also temporarily stopped vehicles from entering the restricted road section , queuing up for the arrival of the 120 first aid vehicles .
at about 1500 hours , an ambulance with a Chuan U licence plate entered the territory of Beichuan . the traffic police of Beichuan dispatched a police vehicle to drive up the road and escort the ambulance all the way back into the controlled section .
it has been learned that there are places on the circular lake road where only one vehicle can pass through , and the civilian police have exercised temporary control over these places in advance , thus ensuring the smooth passage of 120 first aid vehicles .
upon arrival at the village of 10 li pei , Shiping township , traffic police contacted the two village committees in advance , borrowed the village road to make a detour and banned social vehicles from entering the village .
" it took only 40 minutes for the traffic police in Beichuan to receive the 120 ambulance to enter the normal road of the 302 provincial road . "
in the normal course of events , the entire passage time would take four hours , he said .
" this arrangement has successfully secured valuable treatment time for the patients . "
it has been learned that at 1720 , critically ill people were sent to Mianyang in time for medical treatment .
